post_text: Students at Beechwood Knoll and Lincoln Hancock had a special visitor today for Read Across America...
shared_text:
City of Quincy
February 28 at 3:34 PM ·

Read Across America is an initiative on reading created by the National Education Association that began in 1997. Read Across America Day is observed in U.S. schools on the day closest to Dr. Seuss' birthday of March 2nd.

Mayor Koch read to 3rd grade students at Beechwood Knoll & Lincoln Hancock Elementary Schools this morning in recognition of the classroom celebrations.
